<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="32" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1007,1274]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,272,1007,1033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(after Cook 
<number box="[429,493,1008,1034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1974.0">1974</number>
): Body not compressed, wider than high and without a median dorsal furrow; integument is papillose; dorsalia absent; lateral eyes present but not in capsules; the lenses associated with the integument and widely separated from each other; median eye absent; coxae in four groups; genital flaps well developed and bearing numerous acetabula; no pronounced sexual dimorphism; legs with swimming setae but these reduced in size and number in stream inhabiting species; capitulum with a short rostrum; claws with a clawlet; palp five­segmented; dorsodistal portion of P­ 
<number box="[793,807,1208,1234]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="4.0">4</number>
extending far beyond the base of the fifth segment to form a scissor­like end; distomedial portion of P­ 
<number box="[728,742,1248,1274]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="2.0">2</number>
with pectinate setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
